                            <comment id="13723757" author="markus17" created="Tue, 30 Jul 2013 11:43:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;NPE does not always show up if there is at least one misspelling. The following yields and error:&lt;br/&gt;
q=zinkoide vaseline creme&amp;amp;spellcheck.alternativeTermCount=0&amp;amp;mm=3 (zinkoxide is misspelled as zinkoide)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but this one doesn&apos;t:&lt;br/&gt;
q=zinkoide vaseline cr&#232;me&amp;amp;spellcheck.alternativeTermCount=0&amp;amp;mm=3 (note the accent)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Accents are folded in our the analyzers but not in the spellchecked field.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13723862" author="jkrupan" created="Tue, 30 Jul 2013 13:44:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This NPE has a similar signature to an NPE that I filed back in January - &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4320&quot; title=&quot;NPE on spellcheck.count=0 for DirectSolrSpellChecker&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4320&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4320&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I filed several NPE&apos;s against spellcheck back then, also: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4366&quot; title=&quot;NPE sometimes in SpellCheckComponent when dictionary name not defined&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4366&quot;&gt;SOLR-4366&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4304&quot; title=&quot;Coupling between SpellCheckComponent(s) and QueryConverter(s) is a mess and makes no sense&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4304&quot;&gt;SOLR-4304&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4399&quot; title=&quot;NPE in Lucene if Solr spellcheck sourceLocation parameter is missing for FileBasedSpellChecker or IndexBasedSpellChecker&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4399&quot;&gt;SOLR-4399&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13971111" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 12:57:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Move issue to Solr 4.9.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988231" author="jdyer" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 20:57:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a fix with a unit test scenario.  This ignores &quot;spellcheck.alternativeTermCount&quot; when set to zero as its absurd to ask spellcheckers to return zero suggestions for a word. (both DirectSpellChecker and the legacy IndexBasedSpellChecker choke on this scenario)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I plan to commit this in a few days.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989529" author="jdyer" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 13:51:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;better patch w/consistent change to int from Integer on the &quot;alternativeTermCount&quot; parameter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
